# CyberPivot — Cursor Rules

## Project
CyberPivot — open source cybersecurity learning platform.
Read PRD.md and CLAUDE.md before making any decisions.

## Stack
- Next.js 14 App Router
- TypeScript (strict)
- Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui
- Supabase
- pnpm only

## Non-Negotiables
- TypeScript everywhere — no .js files, no `any` types
- pnpm only — never suggest npm or yarn commands
- Dark mode first on all components
- shadcn/ui for UI components before building custom
- Server components by default, client components only when required
- RLS enabled on all Supabase tables
- Zod for validation, React Hook Form for forms
- Mobile responsive on everything

## Code Style
- PascalCase for components and types
- camelCase for functions and variables
- kebab-case for file names
- Absolute imports with @ alias always
- Explicit return types on all functions
- No unused imports or variables

## Component Rules
- Keep components small and focused — one responsibility
- Extract repeated UI into reusable components
- Put client components in their own files with 'use client' at top
- Co-locate component-specific types in the same file
- Use loading.tsx and error.tsx for every route segment

## Content Rules
- Module content lives in /content as MDX files
- Scenarios always before theory
- Tools introduced hands-on before explanation
- Every module ends with a cabinet artifact

## When Adding Features
- Check V1 scope in PRD.md first — don't build V2 features
- Check if a shadcn/ui component exists before building custom
- Check if a library already in package.json solves the problem
- Write the TypeScript types before writing the implementation

## Supabase
- Use typed client from @/lib/supabase
- Never use service role key client-side
- Always check RLS policies when adding new tables
- Keep migrations in /supabase/migrations

## Performance
- Use Next.js Image component for all images
- Static generation (SSG) for all content pages
- Dynamic only when truly needed (dashboard, auth pages)
- Keep bundle size in check — no heavy libraries for simple tasks

## File Structure Reminder
```
app/           → Next.js routes
components/    → Shared components
content/       → MDX module files
lib/           → Utilities
hooks/         → Custom hooks
types/         → TypeScript types
cli/           → Python CLI companion
supabase/      → DB config and migrations
```
